main event: A white object with a red stripe was observed in Louisville, Kentucky, for 45 minutes on 13 November 1957.
interesting points: The object was seen moving very fast, The sighting lasted for 45 minutes, The object has been observed over a period of one week, The report suggests the object was probably Venous, There is a second reported sighting of a circular bright object lasting 3 to 5 minutes.
sighted object: white object with a red stripe
